From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] Start venus-mdns-aliases alongside avahi-daemon

Launches venus-mdns-aliases as a background process after avahi-daemon
starts. It publishes venus-<portalid>.local and venus-<serial>.local as
CNAME records pointing to venus.local, so clients can reliably find a
specific GX device by name even when multiple devices share the same
subnet. CNAMEs are used rather than A records so that IP changes are
handled automatically via avahi's own per-interface hostname tracking.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [Venus specific]
---
 initscript/debian/avahi-daemon.in | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/initscript/debian/avahi-daemon.in b/initscript/debian/avahi-daemon.in
--- a/initscript/debian/avahi-daemon.in
+++ b/initscript/debian/avahi-daemon.in
@@ -137,2 +137,3 @@ d_start() {
     $DAEMON -D --no-chroot
+    venus-mdns-aliases &
 }
@@ -144,2 +145,3 @@ d_stop() {
     $DAEMON -c && $DAEMON -k
+    pkill -f venus-mdns-aliases 2>/dev/null || true
 }
